  "text": "CSS calc() in Firefox is parsed by Servo (Rust) in specified/calc.rs, with the generic resolution algorithm in generics/calc.rs (handling NaN, infinity, overflow in arithmetic operations like Sum, Product, MinMax, Clamp, Round, ModRem). The computed value resolution occurs in computed/length_percentage.rs (CalcLengthPercentage::resolve) which applies AllowedNumericType clamping and NaN normalization. The C++ side consumes these via FFI: ServoStyleConstsInlines.h provides LengthPercentage::Resolve() and StyleCalcLengthPercentage::Resolve() which call Servo_ResolveCalcLengthPercentage (in glue.rs), then convert the float result to nscoord using DefaultPercentLengthToAppUnits/DefaultLengthToAppUnits with overflow clamping. gfx/src/nsCoord.h provides the low-level saturating/clamped arithmetic (NSToCoordTruncClamped, NSCoordSaturatingAdd, etc.) that prevents integer overflow when extreme calc() values are converted to app units. nsStyleStruct.cpp contains the C++ StyleCalcNode::ScaleLengthsBy for DPI scaling of calc nodes.",
